The paper deals with the problem of finding sparse representations of signals in pairs of bases, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.IT, cs.SP). The specific bases considered in the paper are Fourier and canonical bases, which are commonly used in signal processing and image analysis (cs.SP, cs.LG). The paper also introduces a polynomial complexity algorithm for finding sparse representations, which involves optimization and numerical methods (cs.MM, cs.NA).
